In general. (B) Specified method potentially applicable. (C) No specified method applicable. (iii) Documentation requirement. (A) In general. (B) Principal and background documents. (4) Certain foreign to foreign transactions. (5) Special rule. (6) Examples. (e) Special rules in the case of carrybacks and carryovers. (f) Rules for coordinating between the transactional penalty and the net adjustment penalty. (1) Coordination of a net section 482 adjustment subject to the net adjustment penalty and a gross valuation misstatement subject to the transactional penalty. (2) Coordination of net section 482 adjustment subject to the net adjustment penalty and substantial valuation misstatements subject to the transactional penalty. (3) Examples. (g) Effective date. Par. 3. Section 1.6662&hyph;5T is added to read as follows: §1.6662&hyph;5T Substantial and gross valuation misstatements under chapter 1 (temporary).
